The paper deals with the application of non-orthogonal multiple access (NOMA) in downlink multiuser multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) cellular systems, which involves techniques related to information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), control and systems engineering (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and computer communication (cs.COM). The paper discusses user clustering, beamforming, and power allocation, which are relevant to these sub-categories.
